en_content:
AGI - The city of Kharkiv under attack by Russian drones in the early hours of Thursday 4 April. According to Telegram from Oleh Syniehubov Oblast Governor, four people were killed and six were wounded. To lose life - reports Kyiv Independent - were three operators of the emergency service that were on the scene for rescues in response to a previous Russian attack, as well as a civilian. Five more civilians and an emergency service operator were injured due to other drone attacks. Other explosions have been heard in the city: damaged houses and multi-storey buildings.&nbsp;
