AGI - The White House has been called "indignated" for the killing of seven humanitarian workers in Gaza, who were mistakenly affected by the Israeli armed forces. President Joe Biden entertained himself with the founder of the World Central Kitchen, the Spanish Josè Andres, who belonged to the victims. The White House spokesman, Karine Jean Pierre, reported that the president has "the broken heart" for the event and that he will reaffirm with Israel the need for "humanitarian operators to be protected". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
For his part, the United Kingdom Foreign Ministry convened the Israeli ambassador to London: of the seven operators killed three were British.&nbsp;"I requested a rapid and transparent investigation, shared with the international community, and full responsibility," said Undersecretary of Foreign Affairs Andrew Mitchell in a note after the meeting with the Israeli ambassador in London.&nbsp;
